doneThe task required transforming a 1-million-row CSV file using Vim macros. I developed a macro that performs the following steps:
1. Removes all spaces using `:s/ //g`.
2. Replaces commas with semicolons using `:s/,/;/g`.
3. Reorders the three columns using a regex substitution: `:s/\([^;]*\);\([^;]*\);\([^;]*\)/\3;\2;\1/`.
4. Appends `;OK` to the end of each line.
5. Converts the entire line to uppercase using `:s/\(.*\)/\U\1/`.

The macro was implemented by setting the register `a` with the exact sequence of keystrokes (including carriage returns `\x0d`) to ensure it runs correctly in a headless environment. The script `/app/apply_macros.vim` was created and executed via `vim -Nu NONE -n -Es /app/input.csv -S /app/apply_macros.vim`, resulting in a byte-for-byte match with `/app/expected.csv`.

